    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-04-11T13:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-04-11T13:30:00-05:00" n="773"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d773">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.857 Hannover/14: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-11T14:00:00-04:30"
                            >April 11, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:33 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>36. Department’s circular April 6, 3 p.m. The Mexican [<hi rend="italic"
                        >Venezuelan?</hi>] Minister for Foreign Affairs reaffirmed the position of
                    his Government that the correct method of procedure is by submission of all
                    protests to the Rio Neutrality Committee (please see last paragraph of
                    memorandum transmitted with my despatch 230, February 21, 1940<note n="41"
                        xml:id="d773fn41">Not printed.</note>). He has communicated with Dr. Garay
                    to this effect.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
